Scheme Annual Report 2015 - 2016SBI Arbitrage Opportunities FundSBI ARBITRAGE OPPORTUNITIES FUNDSID - SBI Arbitrage Opportunities FundKIM - SBI Arbitrage Opportunities Fund







Inefficiencies arise in the market when the same asset has a price differential between two or more market segments. Arbitrage funds take advantage of these opportunitiesSBI Arbitrage Opportunities Fund aims to provide capital appreciation and regular income for unit holders by identifying profitable arbitrage opportunities between the spot and derivative market segments as also through investment of surplus cash in debt and money market instruments. It seeks to exploit such inefficiencies that will manifest as mispricing in cash (stock) and derivative markets. The fund adopts a market neutral trading strategy. The scheme will seize arbitrage opportunities by buying stock in the spot market of NSE or BSE and simultaneously selling futures on the same stock in F&O segment of NSE when the price of the future exceeds the price of the stock. The Fund Manager will lock into such arbitrage opportunities seeking to generate tax efficient risk free returns.The fund is suitable for investors with low to medium risk appetite looking for excess earnings from risk free arbitrage opportunities that arise from imbalances between two or more markets.









Enter Date  * : 







