Arbitrage - Definition of the Trading Term Arbitrage



daytrading.about.com
Arbitrage.


Definition: 

Arbitrage is the process of buying and selling an identical (or very similar) financial instrument at the same time on different markets. For example, exchanging British Pounds (GBP) for US Dollars (USD) in London
